      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "MAX models can now run on Apple silicon GPUs",
      "url": "https://forum.modular.com/t/max-models-can-now-run-on-apple-silicon-gpus/3283",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/4srepl",
      "score": 5,
      "comments": 4,
      "author": "melodyogonna",
      "published": "2026-06-28T09:21:19Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Modular's MAX Engine now supports Apple Silicon GPUs, enabling high-performance local inference on M-series chips using unified memory.",
        "The update allows Mojo-based pipelines to leverage Apple's Metal API, bypassing CPU bottlenecks for low-latency model execution.",
        "AI practitioners can deploy optimized models like Llama 3 locally on Macs, reducing reliance on costly cloud GPU instances."
      ]
    },
